  lede:"Eight neurodiverse minds learn to play chess. They play each other non-stop, evolve, remember rivals and dream. Each is a different kind of genius, not a label. Watch the live ranking or sit down for a game against one of them.",
  "s.games":"games played","s.leader":"ranking leader","s.age":"tournament running","s.live":"live","s.boards":"4 boards · 24/7",
  "b.eye":"Tournament tables","b.h":"Four games right now","b.p":"Every move is real, legal chess. The eight pick their own opponents.",
  "r.eye":"The eight minds","r.h":"Each plays differently, because each thinks differently","r.p":"A different cognitive style = different evaluation, depth, temperature and appetite for risk. Over time the weaker learn from the stronger and evolve in their sleep.",
